# Copy to .env and set for production frontend builds.
# Public URL of the Express API (no trailing slash). Required when the app is served
# from S3/CloudFront so /api requests hit your backend instead of static HTML.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com
#
# Deploy-time: `npm run deploy:frontend` always writes dist/api-runtime-config.js.
# Optional override:
# Production frontend: set before `npm run deploy:frontend` so API calls do not hit S3 on CloudFront:
#   export HR_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-express-host.example.com:5001
# If unset, users must set the API URL once on the login screen (saved in hr_api_base_url).
# If unset, this repo defaults to the Life Smile CloudFront origin (same host; /api/* → Express).
#
# Without rebuilding: set window.__HR_API_BASE_URL__ in public/api-runtime-config.js
# (that file is copied to dist root; upload it next to index.html).
# Or in production the login page prompts once and saves the URL in localStorage (hr_api_base_url).
#
# If you use same-origin /api via CloudFront (no VITE_API_BASE_URL), see:
# docs/cloudfront-api-routing.md
